      "created": 1346012587485,
      "updated": 0,
      "title": "A good choice for its class",
      "text": "I just upgraded from my 2010 A4 to the 2013. The 8-speed automatic provides smoother acceleration and better mileage (averaging over 25mpg in mixed driving). They fixed some of the annoying bugs in the \"Infotainment\" system. However I was disappointed to see the folding rear seats move to the premium plus package. The new brown interior is ill-conceived. Should have been a lighter saddle-brown as offered in the BMW. Overall, it's a good value for the class, and works better for me than the 3-series.",
      "favoriteFeatures": "Fuel-efficient and peppy 4 cylinder turbo engine. Comfortable interior size. Good build quality. Delivered stereo sounds decent. Nicely equipped without having to option up. Nice looking car. ",
      "suggestedImprovements": "Disappointed to see the folding rear seats leave the premium trim for the premium plus. The flexibility was a big advantage. Brown interior needs to be reconsidered (lighten the shade). Although improved, the electronic interface is still a bit buggy.",
