      "title": "8000 mile update",
      "text": "Wanted to update my review first made shortly after purchase.\nHave owned the vehicle for 8 months now and continue to be impressed by it.\nNo problems after 8000 miles.\nCar was virtually unstopable in heavy snow (with 4 Pirelli snows mounted) this past winter.\nI average 26-28 mpg in mixed drving; best tank 34 mpg highway at 70 mph.\nDespite what some others have noticed, the engine has not consumed any oil in its first 8000 miles.\nBreak the engine in as directed in the manual and there should not be any problem.\n",
      "favoriteFeatures": "8 speed automatic is intuitive and responsive; \"S\" mode livens the car up dramatically by holding lower gears and speeding up throttle response making the driving experience that much more fun; beautiful, high quality interior; complete keyless access with push button start; voice commands that work seamlessly",
      "suggestedImprovements": "spring loaded fuel filler door is cheap; HVAC controls more cumbersome for manual control than they need to be; that's about it",
